<HL>
   Business Brief -- Reckitt &amp; Colman PLC:
   Company Says Pretax Profit
   Rose 15% for the 1st Half
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.RCO
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
CONSUMER AND HOUSEHOLD PRODUCTS (HPR)
</IN>
<LP>
   Reckitt &amp; Colman PLC said pretax profit rose 15% for the
first half of the year, with strong Continental European and
Latin American earnings offsetting a decline in the U.K.
   The British food and household goods maker said pretax
profit rose to #113 million ($215.3 million) from #98.6
million in the year-earlier period, comfortably within market
expectations which ranged between #110 million to #115
million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Profit after tax and minority interests increased by 15%
to #71.9 million pounds from #62.4 million. Per-share
earnings rose to 47.8 pence from 42.0 pence.
   Net profit attributable to shareholders rose 7% to #65.8
million from #61.5 million. Reckitt &amp; Colman reported an
extraordinary loss of #5.33 million in the latest figure; in
last year's period, the company had an extraordinary loss of
#780,000.
   The company said it would raise its half-year dividend by
15% to 12.25 pence from 10.65 pence.
   Reckitt &amp; Colman said sales rose 14% to #843 million from
#737 million.
</TEXT>
